      },
      "lineNbr": 141,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-03-31T16:28:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Better typing would call this a mach_header_64. Use \u003cdyld/loader.h\u003e. Do the same for other things you get from Dl_info::dli_fbase.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 141,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 141,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "a191cbdf84fc2b4935af3ca7ecff30498571a2cb",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "50626549_805fec07",
        "filename": "util/ios/exception_processor.mm",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 143,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-03-31T16:28:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good news!\n\nSince this is involved in the handling of Objective-C exceptions, and none of the C standard library is implemented in Objective-C, it’s entirely safe to use things like logging in here. You don’t need to exercise the same caution that you would in a signal handler.\n\nThat means that if this fails, you can:\n\n  LOG(ERROR) \u003c\u003c \"dladdr: \" \u003c\u003c dlerror();",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 142,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 143,
        "endChar": 30
      },
      "revId": "a191cbdf84fc2b4935af3ca7ecff30498571a2cb",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "dc9cbffc_dc84bb0a",
        "filename": "util/ios/exception_processor.mm",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 145,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-03-31T16:28:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I’m sure that there’s a better way to get this, but Apple has made the “better way” still be about as much typing as this. I’m trying to think of whether there’s a way that’s both better AND easier.\n\nOptionally factor this into a static variable so it only needs to be computed once.\n\n  static void* this_base_address \u003d [](){\n    Dl_info dl_info;\n    // …\n    return dl_info.dli_fbase;\n  }();",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 139,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 145,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "a191cbdf84fc2b4935af3ca7ecff30498571a2cb",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
